summary: An ordinance accepting deeds from Susan B. Armstrong, a widow; Ralph S. Stacy, as Treasurer of King County, Washington; A. B. Stone, a widower; F. J. Darnell and Jessie F. Darnell, his wife; and Nellie D. Banta, a widow; to the City of Seattle, for street and alley purposes, and laying off 32nd Avenue Southwest, 34th Avenue Southwest, West Holly Street, West Willow Street and a public alley.
